title: Nigeria Capacity Utilization
description: Capacity Utilization in Nigeria decreased to 51.30 percent in the second quarter of 2022 from 55.40 percent in the first quarter of 2022. Capacity Utilization in Nigeria averaged 54.57 percent from 2009 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 60.50 percent in the first quarter of 2015 and a record low of 40.10 percent in the second quarter of 2020. This page provides - Nigeria Capacity Utilization- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Nigeria
